		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1462278">Our prison population is another of those barely noticed tragedies that goes on around us.<br />
While the 1 in 100 is bad (approximate actual number in prison) in some demographics it's horrifying. 1 in 9 black men is in prison as I write this. 1 in 30 men in the entire population is in prison (something like 1 in 300 women).<br />
For drugs, 10-20% (depending on state, federal) were incarcerated for drug offenses. Around 50% for violent crimes.<br />
About 2.6% of the prison population is HIV positive, over triple the national average.<br />
About 32% of black men will be in prison at some point during their lives, vs. around 5% for white men.<br />
<br />
Edit for one last factoid: The prison population over the past 3 years grew faster then the overall population......<br />
<br />
<br />
cite for a lot of this data <a href="http://drugwarfacts.org/cms/?q=node/64" target="_blank">http://drugwarfacts.org/cms/?q=node/64</a></div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
